headline: India plans sweeping consumption tax cuts by October to boost economy
summary: NEW DELHI (Reuters) -India's government will slash the consumption tax it charges consumers and businesses by October, a top official said on Friday, hours after Prime Minister Narendra Modi announced sweeping tax reforms to boost the economy in the face of a trade conflict with Washington.  The federal government will propose a two-rate structure of 5% and 18%, doing away with the 12% and 28% tax that was imposed on some items, said the government official, who declined to be named as the plans are still private.  Modi on Friday made a public appeal to promote domestic products, and his supporters have been calling for boycott of American products.
